Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping toldvisiting U.S. Secretary of State George Shultz China's recenttroubles were over.    The two discussed Washington's scandal over U.S. Arms salesto Iran and China's political situation after the fall ofCommunist Party leader Hu Yaobang.    Deng said: "I know the President has had some difficultiesbut I think now it doesn't matter. When one is running agovernment one has to deal with troubles."    "As for the troubles we recently encountered, they are over,"Deng added. REUTER&#3;